        "text": "Matthew 5:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". A repetition depending here, no doubt, on Mark (Weiss), yet not to be regarded as out of place, because the proverbial saying refers to one’s own temptations as coming through the senses, while here the point in question is the temptation of others (de Wette, Kuinoel, Strauss, Holtzmann, Hilgenfeld), but on the contrary as quite appropriate, inasmuch as the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "σκάνδαλα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " occasioned from without operate through the senses, and thereby seduce into evil.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
